int number2=Integer.parseInt(req.getParameter(&quot;num2&quot;));
```
Java will not be able to parse `int` from parameter if parameter is `null` or not a number. In your particular case one of the parameters is `null`. But generally, as it&#39;s a user input, you need to validate if parameters `num1` and `num2` can be parsed or you need to catch an exception and process it (show meaningful error like &quot;Please input correct data&quot; etc.). You may check this [question][1], you&#39;ll get the idea. 

