You can use a custom project repository 

    &lt;!– In Project repository –&gt;
    &lt;repository&gt;
        &lt;id&gt;in-project&lt;/id&gt;
        &lt;name&gt;In Project Repo&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;url&gt;file://${project.basedir}/libs&lt;/url&gt;
    &lt;/repository&gt;

and then call your jar

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;sapjco3&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;sapjco3&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;1.3.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

another option is put the jar file in your .m2 folder, but is not a good practice. You can read this article [how to add a custom jar in maven][1].

Other way is add the path of your jar on the dependency block:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;sapjco3&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;com.sapjco3&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;1.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;system&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;systemPath&gt;${project.basedir}/src/main/resources/sapjco3.jar&lt;/systemPath&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

I hope it helps.


